The four advances integrated into the SHERLOCKv2 platform are:
1) Adaptation of the Java Molecular Viewer (JMV) to virtual reality display environments;
2) Overlay of phylogenetic information derived from multiple alignments onto molecule structures;
3) Ability to change the number of sequences included in the underlying multiple alignment for dynamical updates of the displayed information; and
4) Extension to handle an infinite number of objects (molecules) in the same display with the ability to manipulate them in six degrees of freedom simultaneously or independently.
